The Spinnex material utilizes a minimum of 30% surplus textile waste, regrind speckles in the overlays contain scrap TPU, and the midsole includes 5% EVA regrind.

  • - Partially Recycled Insole: The dual density insert consists of a foam in a heel carrier. The insert foam is made of a combination of 6% castor bean oil, 15% recycled foam, 5% recycled rubber, and 74% virgin PU. The heel carrier is made from 98% post-production leftover foam and rubber.
  • - Recycled Content Upper Canvas: The canvas and overlays have been coated in a TPU that contains a regrind speckle. This regrind is made from scrap TPU left over from the TPU film making process.

  • - Regrind rubber and recycled Crater foam underfoot feel soft and add speckles of color for a 1-of-a-kind look and feel. The recycled insole feels like a new bed for your foot.
  • - The stitched on webbing eyestays and embroidered Swoosh create a modern aesthetic and add to the deconstructed design, which lets manufacturing go faster to reduce the carbon imprint.
  • - The updated Waffle sole design adds Nike heritage with a modern twist.
  • - The pinwheel logo lets you know this shoe is made from at least 50% recycled materials.

  • - Pinwheel logo indicates that this shoe is made from at least 50% recycled materials
